==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diaphanous
<hw>Di*aph"a*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr.
<?/ to show or shine through; <grk>dia`</grk> through + <?/ to show, and
in the passive, to shine: cf. F. <ets>diaphane</ets>. See
<er>Phantom</er>, and cf. <er>Diaphane</er>, <er>Diaphanic</er>.]</ety>
<def>Allowing light to pass through, as porcelain; translucent or
transparent; pellucid; clear.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Another cloud in the region of them, light enough to be fantastic
and <qex>diaphanous</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Landor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diaphanously</ent>⟦br⟧
